According to BirdLife International, the population of the species is estimated at 210 thousand individuals and continues to decrease [2][4]. organizations, 287 birds live in Utah, 37 in Nevada, 703 in Idaho, 4,912 in California, and 68,509 in British Columbia. In the 1990s, no birds were noted, and thus their number in these regions was equal to zero. These figures were extrapolated to other regions in which the black american swift lives - Mexico, Central America, the Antilles.